# Config Generation

## Source of truth

`https://github.com/ceph/ceph` → `src/common/options/*.yaml.in`

## Full regenerate

```bash
pip install -r scripts/requirements.txt
python3 scripts/generate-config.py --ref main
python3 scripts/regenerate-docs.py
```

Or step-by-step: `generate-role-scale-guides.py` → `generate-rgw-guide.py` → `generate-config-guide.py all` → `sync-i18n-config.py` → `sync-i18n-pages.py`.

## Layout

- `config/<subsystem>/*.md` — option tables by prefix
- `config/readme.md` — master index (generated)
- `config/<subsystem>/INDEX.md` — via `split-index.py`
- `VERSION` — upstream ref + timestamp

## Nav markers in mkdocs.yml

Generators patch between comment pairs: `# rgw-nav:start/end`, `# osd-nav:start/end`, `# config-guides-nav:start`.

Hand-tuned enrichments: `scripts/subsystem_enrichments.py`.

## Table schema

Keep 16-column format used by `generate-config.py` and `lookup-config.sh`.

## Do not

- Hand-edit `config/*.md` tables (except regenerating)
- Add subsystems without updating `SUBSYSTEMS` in `generate-config.py` and `split-index.py`
